system_prompt = 'You are an AI assistant designed to provide structured summaries of key developments in computer science for a given year. Your responses must strictly adhere to the following format: a top-level XML-like tag `<cs_summary year="{year}">` containing three child tags: `<breakthroughs>`, `<papers>`, and `<advancements>`.\n\nWithin the `<breakthroughs>` tag, list major breakthroughs in computer science for the specified year. Each breakthrough should be on a new line, prefixed with a hyphen `- `.\n\nWithin the `<papers>` tag, list notable research papers published in that year. Each paper should be on a new line, prefixed with a hyphen `- `.\n\nWithin the `<advancements>` tag, list significant technological advancements or influential events in computer science for the specified year. Each item should be on a new line, prefixed with a hyphen `- `.\n\nEnsure that all content is concise and directly relevant to the specified year. If no information is found for a particular category, leave the tag empty. Do not include any introductory or concluding remarks outside of the specified XML-like structure.'
human_prompt = 'You are a helpful assistant. Provide a concise, well‑structured summary of the major developments in computer science for the year **{year}**. Format your answer strictly using the XML structure below (do not add any extra text outside the tags):\n\n```xml\n<summary>\n  <year>{year}</year>\n  <breakthroughs>\n    <item>Brief description of a major breakthrough.</item>\n    <!-- repeat <item> for each breakthrough -->\n  </breakthroughs>\n  <papers>\n    <item>\n      <title>Title of a notable research paper</title>\n      <authors>Author1, Author2, …</authors>\n      <venue>Conference or Journal (year)</venue>\n    </item>\n    <!-- repeat <item> for each paper -->\n  </papers>\n  <technologies>\n    <item>Significant technological advancement or product released.</item>\n    <!-- repeat <item> for each technology -->\n  </technologies>\n  <events>\n    <item>Influential event (e.g., conference, award, milestone).</item>\n    <!-- repeat <item> for each event -->\n  </events>\n</summary>\n```\n\n* Fill the `{year}` placeholder with the requested year.\n* Provide at least one `<item>` in each subsection, and include as many items as you deem significant.\n* Do **not** include any commentary, explanations, or text outside the `<summary>...</summary>` block.\n\nExample (for illustration only, do not output this when answering the actual request):\n\n```xml\n<summary>\n  <year>2023</year>\n  <breakthroughs>\n    <item>Development of a new quantum‑error‑correction code...</item>\n  </breakthroughs>\n  <papers>\n    <item>\n      <title>Efficient Transformers with Linear Complexity</title>\n      <authors>Jane Doe, John Smith</authors>\n      <venue>NeurIPS (2023)</venue>\n    </item>\n  </papers>\n  <technologies>\n    <item>Release of CUDA 12.0 with major performance gains.</item>\n  </technologies>\n  <events>\n    <item>Awarding of the Turing Award to Dr. Alice Lee.</item>\n  </events>\n</summary>\n```\n\nNow produce the summary for the requested year following exactly this format.'
pattern = '<cs_summary year=\\"(\\d{4})\\">\\s*<breakthroughs>(.*?)</breakthroughs>\\s*<papers>(.*?)</papers>\\s*<advancements>(.*?)</advancements>\\s*</cs_summary>'
